          "Attendance Records, \nLMS logs",
          "[Total posts initiated by a student, Total posts and replies by a student, Number of posts in first half of the course, Number of posts in second half of the course, Total times forum was read, Total hits on recourses, Total hits on course information, Total course hits, Total views before course started, Number of hits in first half of course, Number of hits in second half of course, Number of resources accessed, Total logins, Logins in first half of course, Logins in second half of course, Formative assessment grade, Mid-course formative assessment grade, Number attempts formative quizz, End of Course Assessment Grade, Response to Communication, Total views of news forum]",
          "End of Course",
          "Data is taken and aggregated into a dataset. \n\nThe authors identify 64 potential features but ultimately decide keeping smaller subset. These are aggregated into:\n\n1. Interaction and Content Creation, \n2. Hits and Views, \n3. Logins and Course Access, \n4. Time, \n5. Formative Assessment, \n6. Communications\n\n",
          "Automatic Linear Regression, \nLogistic Regression",
          "None",
          "{Sensitivity: 0.81 - Logistic Regression, AUC: 0.90 - Logistic Regression, Recall: 0.808 - Logistic Regression, Accuracy: 0.947 - Logistic Regression}",
          "Authors attempt to apply a Predictive Modeling pipeline to a dataset of Health Students. \n\nThey look at the Pearson correlation between features and final score on the course to select most relevant predictors. \n\nEngagement indicators have consistent and significantly higher correlations with student performance. \n\n",
          "No model assessment strategy for generalizability.\n\nSmall sample.\n\nSmall number of algorithms for comparison. \n\nParameters used are self-described as generic.\n\nNeed for additional sources of data.\n\nVery imbalanced ddataset.\n\n\n"
        ],
